<h2 id="guidelines">Guidelines</h2>
<h3 id="polish">Polish matters</h3>
<p>Don't underestimate the value of these tags. Browsers are more able to embed your website into the OS experience when these simple tags are found in your page. Users expect this integrated look.</p>
<h3 id="unfurl">Unfurling</h3>
<p>When you share a link in a social product like Twitter, iMessage, or Slack, it "unfurls" into a little preview. These head tags and many more are required for a good preview. Slack coined the term and has an
  <a href="https://medium.com/slack-developer-blog/everything-you-ever-wanted-to-know-about-unfurling-but-were-afraid-to-ask-or-how-to-make-your-e64b4bb9254" target="_blank" rel="noopener">in-depth
    article</a> about how this works.</p>
